{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781458415517,"sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_Ff5TfWREBH7jU1o3j1d42480","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-open-design-terminal-and-interface-integration/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-open-design-terminal-and-interface-integration/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.executor-state/\n\n(1 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".executor-state/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-open-design-terminal-and-interface-integration/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro","entries":[".executor-state/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-open-design-terminal-and-interface-integration/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro","time":{"start":1781458415515,"end":1781458415517}},"id":"prt_ec7322d59001uIMK1GCflq45w4","sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","messageID":"msg_ec73221d50014VQrMAv65JJLVa"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781458415914,"sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_PWrLsPfpiezrcxZhHg5U0677","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Outputs\n14: \n15: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n26: \n27: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n28: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n29: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n30: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n31: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n32: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n33: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n35: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n36: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n41: \n42: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: Review verdict: PASS\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ```text\n49: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ```text\n53: Review verdict: FAIL\n54: ```\n55: \n56: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n61: \n62: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n63: \n64: - Current iteration and next focus.\n65: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n66: - Dimension coverage.\n67: - Convergence trend.\n68: - Gate blockers.\n69: - Provisional verdict.\n70: \n71: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n76: \n77: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n78: \n79: - Executive summary.\n80: - Planning trigger.\n81: - Active finding registry.\n82: - Remediation workstreams.\n83: - Spec seed.\n84: - Plan seed.\n85: - Traceability status.\n86: - Deferred items.\n87: - Audit appendix.\n88: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n93: \n94: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n95: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n96: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":96,"totalLines":96,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1781458415910,"end":1781458415913}},"id":"prt_ec7322fbb001ISH1o81wdUuSwZ","sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","messageID":"msg_ec73221d50014VQrMAv65JJLVa"}}
