{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781458539030,"sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_HDJENDoTooUA4WHJOTcu5356","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/graph-metadata.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/graph-metadata.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"schema_version\": 2,\n3:   \"skill_id\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n4:   \"family\": \"mcp\",\n5:   \"category\": \"mcp-tool\",\n6:   \"edges\": {\n7:     \"depends_on\": [\n8:       {\n9:         \"target\": \"sk-interface-design\",\n10:         \"weight\": 0.7,\n11:         \"context\": \"When an Open Design read or run feeds a design decision, apply sk-interface-design's anti-default judgment before deciding\"\n12:       }\n13:     ],\n14:     \"enhances\": [\n15:       {\n16:         \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n17:         \"weight\": 0.3,\n18:         \"context\": \"Reused Open Design tokens and components feed application code that sk-code governs, wires and verifies\"\n19:       }\n20:     ],\n21:     \"siblings\": [\n22:       {\n23:         \"target\": \"mcp-figma\",\n24:         \"weight\": 0.55,\n25:         \"context\": \"Sibling terminal-driven design tool with a daemon model, gated mutating verbs, and an sk-interface-design handoff\"\n26:       }\n27:     ],\n28:     \"conflicts_with\": [],\n29:     \"prerequisite_for\": []\n30:   },\n31:   \"manual\": {\n32:     \"depends_on\": [],\n33:     \"related_to\": [\n34:       \"sk-interface-design\",\n35:       \"sk-code\",\n36:       \"mcp-chrome-devtools\",\n37:       \"mcp-figma\"\n38:     ]\n39:   },\n40:   \"domains\": [\n41:     \"design-systems\",\n42:     \"design-to-code\",\n43:     \"local-first\",\n44:     \"cli\",\n45:     \"mcp\",\n46:     \"open-design\"\n47:   ],\n48:   \"intent_signals\": [\n49:     \"open design\",\n50:     \"open-design\",\n51:     \"od cli\",\n52:     \"od mcp\",\n53:     \"design system from open design\",\n54:     \"drive open design from the terminal\",\n55:     \"local-first design\",\n56:     \"claude design alternative\"\n57:   ],\n58:   \"derived\": {\n59:     \"trigger_phrases\": [\n60:       \"open design\",\n61:       \"open-design\",\n62:       \"od mcp\",\n63:       \"od cli\",\n64:       \"design system from open design\",\n65:       \"drive open design from the terminal\"\n66:     ],\n67:     \"key_topics\": [\n68:       \"od CLI (daemon-cli.mjs)\",\n69:       \"stdio MCP server wiring\",\n70:       \"Open Design daemon and socket model\",\n71:       \"design-system read and reuse\",\n72:       \"multi-turn generation (start_run plus discovery form) and gated verbs\",\n73:       \"od run verbs and od ui respond\",\n74:       \"HTTP API surface and ephemeral port rotation\",\n75:       \"live tools/list verification\",\n76:       \"sk-interface-design integration\"\n77:     ],\n78:     \"intent_signals\": [\n79:       \"open design\",\n80:       \"od mcp\",\n81:       \"od cli\",\n82:       \"design system\",\n83:       \"terminal design\",\n84:       \"headless run\",\n85:       \"start_run\",\n86:       \"local-first design\"\n87:     ],\n88:     \"key_files\": [\n89:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/SKILL.md\",\n90:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/README.md\",\n91:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/od_cli_reference.md\",\n92:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n93:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md\",\n94:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n95:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n96:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n97:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md\",\n98:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md\"\n99:     ],\n100:     \"entities\": [\n101:       {\n102:         \"name\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n103:         \"kind\": \"skill\",\n104:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/SKILL.md\",\n105:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n106:       },\n107:       {\n108:         \"name\": \"README\",\n109:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n110:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/README.md\",\n111:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n112:       },\n113:       {\n114:         \"name\": \"od_cli_reference\",\n115:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n116:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/od_cli_reference.md\",\n117:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n118:       },\n119:       {\n120:         \"name\": \"mcp_wiring\",\n121:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n122:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n123:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n124:       },\n125:       {\n126:         \"name\": \"tool_surface\",\n127:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n128:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md\",\n129:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n130:       }\n131:     ],\n132:     \"causal_summary\": \"mcp-open-design teaches a terminal agent (opencode or Claude Code) to drive the installed Open Design desktop app through its od CLI and stdio MCP server instead of the in-app chat. Wire with od mcp install, then read local projects and design-systems, reuse them, or commission gated headless runs. Generation is multi-turn: start_run (or od run start) fires turn 1, which returns a discovery question-form with zero files, and the design is built only after od ui respond answers the form. od artifacts create only adds a file, never a rendered design. The od CLI is daemon-cli.mjs run under Node (not the bundled vela auth client) and the daemon is socket-discovered on an ephemeral port (not a fixed 7456), hosted by the desktop app, which also exposes an HTTP API whose port rotates on restart (rediscover via /api/mcp/install-info). Pairs with sk-interface-design (the design judgment) over the shared claude_design_parity loop, and never vendors Open Design content.\",\n133:     \"source_docs\": [\n134:       \"SKILL.md\",\n135:       \"README.md\",\n136:       \"references/od_cli_reference.md\",\n137:       \"references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n138:       \"references/tool_surface.md\",\n139:       \"feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n140:       \"manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n141:       \"changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n142:       \"changelog/v1.1.0.0.md\",\n143:       \"changelog/v1.2.0.0.md\"\n144:     ],\n145:     \"created_at\": \"2026-06-14T12:30:00Z\",\n146:     \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:50:00Z\"\n147:   }\n148: }\n\n(End of file - total 148 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 2,\n  \"skill_id\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n  \"family\": \"mcp\",\n  \"category\": \"mcp-tool\",\n  \"edges\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-interface-design\",\n        \"weight\": 0.7,\n        \"context\": \"When an Open Design read or run feeds a design decision, apply sk-interface-design's anti-default judgment before deciding\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"enhances\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n        \"weight\": 0.3,\n        \"context\": \"Reused Open Design tokens and components feed application code that sk-code governs, wires and verifies\"\n      }\n    ],","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/graph-metadata.json","text":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 2,\n  \"skill_id\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n  \"family\": \"mcp\",\n  \"category\": \"mcp-tool\",\n  \"edges\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-interface-desig