{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781458545528,"sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_VthqirSPc4U4BZv40d5a9387","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"mcp-open-design v1.2.0.0 - Retire the mcp-magicpath sibling reference\"\n3: ---\n4: \n5: # v1.2.0.0 - Retire the mcp-magicpath sibling reference\n6: \n7: **Released:** 2026-06-14\n8: \n9: The `mcp-magicpath` skill is removed now that this skill drives the installed Open Design app from the terminal and covers the local design-generation usecase. This release drops the now-dead `mcp-magicpath` sibling reference so the related-skill set and graph edges point only at live skills. There is no change to the Open Design transport, the tool surface, or the gating policy.\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## What Changed\n14: \n15: ### Sibling reference dropped\n16: \n17: - SKILL.md removes the `mcp-magicpath` related-skill bullet and the magicpath mention in the Section 8 related-skills prose.\n18: - README drops the `mcp-magicpath` row from the Related Skills table.\n19: - `graph-metadata.json` removes the `mcp-magicpath` siblings edge and removes it from `manual.related_to`. The `mcp-figma` sibling edge and the `sk-interface-design` design-judgment dependency are unchanged.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Notes\n24: \n25: - This is a reference-hygiene release tied to the `mcp-magicpath` deprecation. The Open Design generation flow, the multi-turn `start_run` plus discovery-form behavior corrected in v1.1.0.0, and every verb and gate are unchanged.\n26: - Historical changelog entries are preserved. The shared `claude_design_parity.md` protocol now names this skill as the single generation transport.\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"mcp-open-design v1.2.0.0 - Retire the mcp-magicpath sibling reference\"\n---\n\n# v1.2.0.0 - Retire the mcp-magicpath sibling reference\n\n**Released:** 2026-06-14\n\nThe `mcp-magicpath` skill is removed now that this skill drives the installed Open Design app from the terminal and covers the local design-generation usecase. This release drops the now-dead `mcp-magicpath` sibling reference so the related-skill set and graph edges point only at live skills. There is no change to the Open Design transport, the tool surface, or the gating policy.\n\n---\n\n## What Changed\n\n### Sibling reference dropped\n\n- SKILL.md removes the `mcp-magicpath` related-skill bullet and the magicpath mention in the Section 8 related-skills prose.\n- README drops the `mcp-magicpath` row from the Related Skills table.\n- `graph-metadata.json` removes the `mcp-magicpath` siblings edge and removes it from `manual.related_to`. The `mcp-figma` sibling edge and the `sk-interface-design` design-judgment dependency are unchanged.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"mcp-open-design v1.2.0.0 - Retire the mcp-magicpath sibling reference\"\n---\n\n# v1.2.0.0 - Retire the mcp-magicpath sibling reference\n\n**Released:** 2026-06-14\n\nThe `mcp-magicpath` skill is removed now that this skill drives the installed Open Design app from the terminal and covers the local design-generation usecase. This release drops the now-dead `mcp-magicpath` sibling reference so the related-skill set and graph edges point only at live skills. There is no change to the Open Design transport, the tool surface, or the gating policy.\n\n---\n\n## What Changed\n\n### Sibling reference dropped\n\n- SKILL.md removes the `mcp-magicpath` related-skill bullet and the magicpath mention in the Section 8 related-skills prose.\n- README drops the `mcp-magicpath` row from the Related Skills table.\n- `graph-metadata.json` removes the `mcp-magicpath` siblings edge and removes it from `manual.related_to`. The `mcp-figma` sibling edge and the `sk-interface-design` design-judgment dependency are unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- This is a reference-hygiene release tied to the `mcp-magicpath` deprecation. The Open Design generation flow, the multi-turn `start_run` plus discovery-form behavior corrected in v1.1.0.0, and every verb and gate are unchanged.\n- Historical changelog entries are preserved. The shared `claude_design_parity.md` protocol now names this skill as the single generation transport.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":26,"totalLines":26,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md","time":{"start":1781458545524,"end":1781458545527}},"id":"prt_ec7342a1200136dpk8UXTYrybd","sessionID":"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD","messageID":"msg_ec7341483001F4cTe4K1OMoM2X"}}
